data.title: Eat Your Heart Out
data.text: Weck's is the kind of breakfast eating place that should be in every hamlet, village and city in the USA. Every time I have been there the service has been excellent. Some servers outshine others, but always exceptional. The food is well prepared with variety and the price is unbeatable.

data.title: For the large appetite!
data.text: Week's has several locations in Albuquerque.  The quality, quality and value is consistent in the three (3) locations I have patronized.  The food is "Down Home"....large portions...the servers are friendly and efficient....the  price is fair....and a good value overall.   A good place for a fast  breakfast  meeting....the coffee is good and plentiful.  They are open for breakfast and lunch only.

data.title: Excellent food
data.text: Had occasion to eat there last Friday with 2 friends.  Food was excellent, flavorful, fresh & even though very busy (as usual) they got it to us very fast.  Spiced coffee was excellent too.  Staff was friendly and attentive.  My kind of breakfast place for sure, 5-star!.

data.title: Just Perfect!
data.text: We were at Weck's the week of the Balloon Festival. Everyone local and all who have been there  before definitely like to repeat. The wait was minimal. The food was hot,  tasty and very nicely prepared. The coffee was wonderful!! The time from order to serve was nicely quick, however the food was not fast food quality. We had a very charming efficient server (Meredith perhaps?) and we felt special by the manager who made certain we were delighted. The location was easy to get to, within walking distance from our motel. We'll be repeating! See you next year!!

data.title: Excellent food once you're in.
data.text: Many of the Wecks I've been to are really good almost 100% of the time. We've been to this one several times over the years and have always had great service and really well prepared and well presented breakfasts. Many portions are too big to finish so we take home a box or two almost every time. Breakfast tacos are really good and huge. La paps are always cook just right. Crispy bacon and eggs are also prepared just as ordered every time. I can truthfully say, I've never sent anything back to the chef, once presented to our table. Great job, Wecks.

data.title: Can you actually go wrong with Wecks? Let's see.
data.text: Like so many others, we too really like Weck's! We haven't been there in such a very long time because the lines are always too long for my wife and me. We usually are too hungry to wait! But that's our own fault. Yesterday, as we passed by, I noticed the line wasn't outside yet and this was a good sign! So on to Weck's we went. With my wife ordering the Pappas bowl, I went with a traditional ham and eggs but I added green chile. When we got our food, I was just slightly disappointed as my hash browns and eggs were just Luke warm. But I was so hungry that I just went ahead and ate instead of sending it back. Alway tasty though. So not a huge issue. But what pleased me the most was the service. Our waitress was Erika and the only way she could have been more attentive is if she pulled our car around and wheeled us out to the awaiting vehicle. She truly was awesome! Over the top friendly, great suggestions and even offered me a "to go" cup of their specialty coffee. I wanted to adopt her! The host, sorry but I didn't catch his name, was also extremely friendly to the point that I asked my wife if she knew him. Of course, we will return....It's Weck's! That is, if the line isn't too long. Something like the breakfast not being hot enough was just a fluke and by no means normal for Weck's, so they get a pass from me on that one. Great place...of course.

owner_response.author: DanielleMontoya, Manager at Weck's, responded to this review
owner_response.text:
Thank you for the great review, we appreciate you dining with us and letting us know how we did. Erika is one of our best servers, we will be sure to pass along your compliments.
